      <MissionDescription>Hope for the Heart is a worldwide ministry with a two-fold mission: providing bible-based counsel to renew minds, heal hearts and bring hope to the hurting, while empowering Christians to disciple others.</MissionDescription>
      <SignificantNewProgramServices>0</SignificantNewProgramServices>
      <SignificantChange>0</SignificantChange>
      <Expense>3542652</Expense>
      <Grants>115464</Grants>
      <Description>Broadcast-Hope for the Heart presents clearly scriptural solutions to real world problems by using a counseling approach that is based on the ministry's 100 biblical counseling keys. The ministry produces two daily radio programs: Hope for the Heart, a live, 25-minute teaching program which airs on some 65 radio stations nationwide, and Hope in the Night, a live, two-hour call-in counseling program which airs on 163 stations. Hope in the Night provides direct interaction with troubled listeners, whose problems range from depression to wife abuse, and from self esteem to forgiveness.</Description>
      <Activity2>
        <Expense>1205354</Expense>
        <Revenue>162826</Revenue>
        <Description>Counseling-The counseling call center takes calls from a variety of sources: felt-needs, crisis / suicide, and inbound triage calls from other ministries. In 2010, more than 25,000 call types were received. The call center publishes the monthly partners in prayer letter/calendar to over 1800 prayer partners. Since 2002, the biblical counseling institute has provided God's truth for today's problems to pastors, counselors, chaplains, teachers, and laypeople. In 2010, almost 1,200 attendees received in-depth, interactive teaching based on 100 biblical counseling keys topics. The multimedia format incorporates radio clips of Hope in the Night callers, offering insightful and compassionate answers to life's toughest questions. In June of 2006, Hope for the Heart received accreditation to offer continuing education through the Association of Christian Schools International (ACSI).</Description>
      </Activity2>
      <Activity3>
        <Expense>1448200</Expense>
        <Description>Global Outreach-Through the efforts of translation teams, our biblical counseling keys are being translated into 21 languages. The counseling keys are now being used in 48 nations. In addition, radio broadcasts sponsored by Hope for the Heart now air in over 26 countries. The Hope for the Heart counseling keys have been named "the best selling Christian resource" in one country alone. In one new country, 40 radio stations are now sharing excerpts of the counseling keys with their listeners. For one station alone, this has prompted up to 300 calls a day from people eager to learn more. Hope for the Heart trains groups and individuals in the use and application of the biblical counseling keys to minister to heart felt needs throughout the world. In the U.S., training includes Chinese and Spanish biblical counseling and equipping pregnancy resource centers. Internationally, training continues to expand in the countries with the counseling keys of other foreign language translations.</Description>
      </Activity3>
